Yu'e Bao's income declines, "post-90s" but "retaliatory" to save money?
With the decline of Yu'e Bao's income, the "post-90s" not only did not escape Yu'e Bao, but began to "retaliate" to save money?
The "Yu'e Bao Post-90s Saving Report" (2020 Edition) released by the China New Economic Research Institute and Alipay recently shows that in the first half of the year, the "post-90s" are more likely to save money: the amount of money saved per capita is nearly 40% higher than that in 2019.
Interestingly, the "post-90s" are more inclined to save from a small amount of money, with 60% of the average amount of money saved below 20 yuan...
Saving money with Yu'e Bao has also become the saving habit of the post-90s generation.
Data show that among the 700 million Yu'ebao users, 134 million are "post-90s".
There are 174 million "post-90s" in China, that is to say, about 3 out of every 4 "post-90s" in China are saving money with Yu'e Bao.
At present, the 7-day annualized rate of return of Yu'e Bao and other monetary funds has dropped to about 1.5% from a level higher than 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of saving money for the post-90s generation.
Under the background of the promotion of Yu'e Bao's "saving effect", many young people who are used to using Yu'e Bao have directly transformed into "basic people".
According to Alipay data, as of July 13, the number of new "basic people" on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have realized "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yu'e Bao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of money funds in June.
The report also shows that "post-90s" girls are more inclined to save more money, with an average amount of 20% higher than that of boys; 60% of the users who hold funds on Alipay platform are men, and women tend to choose more stable financial management methods than men.
After saving money, what are the plans of the post-90s generation?
Alipay data show that the "post-90s" have the habit of saving money for their goals, with the largest number of users taking travel as their goal of saving money.
Affected by the epidemic, many "post-90s" saved money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; the reopening of cinemas also provides a new way to switch from saving money to consumption.
