The longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area runs through
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo courtesy of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Company
China News Service, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the small Three Gorges Tunnel of Zhengwan High-speed Railway, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers, was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed railway tunnel with a design speed of 350 km/h among the projects currently under construction in China.
Zhengwan high-speed railway is located in Henan, Hubei and Chongqing provinces and cities, connecting Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railways in the north of Zhengzhou and Chongqing-Wan high-speed railway in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of the riverside channel and Hunan channel in China's "eight vertical and eight horizontal" high-speed railway network.
The small Three Gorges Tunnel of Zhengwan High-speed Railway was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows running through the scene.
Zheng Wangao Railway starts from Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and passes through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City and Xiangyang City, Hubei Province to Wanzhou District, Chongqing City in the southwest. The new line has a total length of about 818 kilometers, a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has been opened for operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which runs through the whole line on the 26th, is a control project of Zhengwan High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, head of Zhengwan High-speed Railway Tunnel Design of China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and design party, the topographic and geological conditions of the small Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex, facing risks such as karst, mud gushing and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Class I high-risk tunnel, and the design and construction of the tunnel are extremely difficult.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey method, geophysical exploration method and advanced drilling method to advance geological prediction, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built, spanning a large karst cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement." Wang Guojun said.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction of the tunnel adopts the combination of dredging and blocking, through the construction of horizontal tunnel guide, grouting to block water, strengthening the support of tunnel structure and the construction of sewage treatment station, which not only ensures the orderly progress of the project, but also avoids the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcomes the construction problems such as large deformation of soft rock with a length of 7 kilometers and multi-outburst mud gushing with a daily maximum water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters.
After the Zhengwan high-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport main channel from southwest China to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast railway channel in southwest China, improve the layout of the regional road network, speed up the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the line, promote coordinated regional development, and promote the implementation of the western development strategy.
Experts say it is unconstitutional to collect immigration data through the U.S. Census for the allocation of seats in the House of Representatives
Some civil rights organizations and several US cities and counties sued the US federal government, saying that the Trump presidential palace's attempt to exclude undocumented immigrants from the US census was unworkable and unconstitutional.
The U.S. Census will determine the allocation of seats in the House of Representatives of the U.S. Congress.
Sarah Brannon, executive lawyer of the American Civil Liberties Union, told VOA, "This will not work."
