In the first half of the year, telecommunication network fraud crimes rose by 70%, and the highest inspection summarized characteristic - Chinanews.com
BEIJING, July 26 According to the website of the Supreme People's Procuratorate, in the first half of this year, procuratorial organs across the country prosecuted 58,101 people for fraud crimes, up 35% year-on-year.
Especially in the crimes hindering the prevention and control of the epidemic, fraud crimes occur frequently, and the number of fraud crimes prosecuted by procuratorial organs accounts for 43.4% of the total number of crimes hindering the prevention and control of the epidemic.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance. Among the ten batches of typical cases involving epidemic prevention and control that have been released so far, there are 9 cases involving fraud.
Judging from the handling of cases by procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are many kinds of fraud crimes, ranging from national macro policies to people's clothing, food, housing and transportation, including epidemic-related fraud, "medical care" fraud, "health care products" fraud, "enrollment intermediary" fraud, "routine loan" fraud, defrauding state subsidies fraud, national assets unfreezing fraud and so on, constantly "innovating", covering education, medical care, employment, old-age care, social security, land acquisition and demolition, precise poverty alleviation, financial credit and other fields, which not only cause economic losses to the victims, but also seriously affect economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunication network frauds break through the restrictions of national boundaries, regions and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholder, cross-border, remote, electronic payment, etc. There are many unspecified victim groups and great harm.
For example, some set up special companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or posts, use legal network platforms to publicize and recruit, train and assess recruiters, adopt enterprise operation mode management, and wear "legal cloak", which is more confusing.
It is the unshirkable responsibility of procuratorial organs to punish and prevent crimes according to law and issue early warnings to the public and relevant departments in a timely manner.
In judicial handling, procuratorial organs conscientiously perform their duties, not only insisting on maintaining a high-pressure situation against fraud crimes, but also refining various law enforcement measures in a targeted manner, and promoting social governance by issuing procuratorial suggestions.
Procuratorial organs strictly control the facts, evidence, procedures and application of law in approving and prosecuting fraud cases, and take facts as the basis and law as the criterion, so as not to waste money.
Especially for telecommunication network fraud crimes, we should pay attention to the core role of electronic data in fact determination, and strive to build an evidence chain of mutual confirmation among electronic data, verbal evidence and documentary evidence.
For example, in the case of an epidemic-related fraud handled by the Yinzhou District Procuratorate of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province, the procuratorial organ intervened in advance at the first time, and it took only five days from the occurrence of the case to its completion, reflecting the attitude and determination to handle it quickly and strictly and maintain the stability of the overall social situation.
In the process of examining arrest and prosecution, attention was paid to the prosecution of missing criminals in cases, correcting 733 missing arrests by public security organs and 1113 missing examination and prosecution of accomplices by public security organs.
In the first half of the year, procuratorial organs across the country issued 298 procuratorial suggestions on fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promoting in-depth governance.
For example, in view of the loopholes found in the supervision of telecommunication networks by communication enterprises, banks, intermediary organizations, etc., Guangzhou Procuratorate and Dongguan Procuratorate of Guangdong Province put forward procuratorial suggestions in time, urging relevant units to strengthen supervision, improve mechanisms, and promote the construction of a long-term system.
The fourth is to do a good job in recovering stolen goods and losses.
Procuratorial organs around the country seize important links such as intervening in investigation, guiding evidence collection, examining and prosecuting, urging investigation organs to actively recover stolen money, cooperating with relevant departments to do a good job in recovering stolen goods and losses, and striving to minimize the economic losses caused by fraud crimes to the people.
For example, in the Lin Moumou routine loan case handled by the Beijing Municipal Procuratorate, the case involved 22 properties waiting to be sealed up. Under the condition that the property may be disposed of first by other cases, it was the first to issue a "suspension letter" and deliver it to the relevant court in a timely manner. It is suggested that the previous seizure court suspend the execution of the property involved and dispose of it uniformly after the criminal facts are found out, so as to make the best efforts to recover the property involved and recover the losses of the victims.
Prosecutors remind everyone to be very vigilant against fraud crimes, not to expect "pie in the sky", not to be credulous because it is cheap, and to keep their "money bags".
Yina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province: Shorter Apple Trees, Broader Road to Poverty Alleviation
2020-07-26 11:42:58 Source: China Economic Net Author: Zhu Yanjing Editor: Zhu Yanjing
In the scorching heat, a reporter from Economic Daily-China Economic Net walked into Zhonghai Village, Yina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province.
Under the scorching sun, villager Li Yuanzhong weeded in the base. Although his face was red in the sun, he hummed a few ditties from time to time.
Weining County, where Yina Town is located, has a certain popularity in the surrounding areas due to its low latitude, high altitude, sufficient light and large temperature difference between day and night. However, due to its small size and many spots, it has not been able to sell at a good price and form an industrial scale.
Yina Town used to be a poor township that "wrapped valley potato for the spring and autumn". Ten years ago, the incidence of local poverty was as high as 25.8%.
In the critical period of getting rid of poverty and entering a decisive battle, it is urgent to change the traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure and increase farmers' income.
After many visits, Chen Chao, secretary of the Party Committee of Yina Town, and a group of people in the town believed that industrial development could no longer follow the old path.
To this end, Yina Town introduced leading enterprises to grow apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Chaoyue Agriculture Co., Ltd., came to Yina Town from Shaanxi Province in 2015 for investigation, took a fancy to the local planting conditions at a glance, and began to plant apple trees locally in 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees. Li Yuanzhong and his wife murmured in their hearts: "After planting apples for so many years, I haven't seen anyone in the village who has grown apples and made a fortune."
"The apples planted are dwarf apples, which will not make the apple trees grow too high."
To Li Yuanzhong's surprise, a new method was adopted for apple planting this time. Irrigation pipes were laid under each apple tree, and water and fertilizer were poured to the roots of the tree. When the fruit was harvested in autumn, the tractor drove directly into the orchard and could pick the fruit standing up.
At present, the Apple base has gradually entered a high-yield period, and the market is as expected by Hou Jianwen. Apple is not worried about selling and is deeply loved by consumers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and other cities.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life. Although he is still farming, he has a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family has more than 9 mu of land transferred to the Apple Base. Every year, in addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee, there is also a profit dividend after hanging the fruit. The couple usually work in the base. "One person can get 80 yuan every day and have work all the year round."
Li Yuanzhong told reporters that last year's profit dividend was more than 2,800 yuan, plus the land transfer fee and the couple's working income, and the family's income was more than 80,000 yuan. "There is no worry about food and clothing, and a well-off life has already lived."
"At present, it has achieved initial results. The annual output value of 1 mu of apples exceeds 15,000 yuan, which is about 10 times that of corn."
Chen Chao told reporters that 20,000 mu of apples have been planted in the whole town of Yina, 6,000 mu in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 households and 17,200 people, including 656 households and 2,952 poor households who have set up files and set up cards. The annual salary is more than 6 million yuan, which really realizes that the base is built at home and there is no need to go out to work.
Li Yuanzhong, whose pockets are bulging day by day, has also begun to realize his "wish".
During the Lunar New Year this year, Li Yuanzhong bought an off-road vehicle and now drives to and from work every day. "There are still more than ten mu of land at home. When the next step is to expand the scale of the Apple base, all of it will be transferred to them, and the income will be even more."
Economic Daily-China Economic Net reporter Wu Bingze Niu Jin Wang Xinwei
