Chengdu people gathered to watch the US consulate police prevent people from "looking too happy"
In response to the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston by the United States, China announced the closure of the US Consulate General in Chengdu on Friday.
On Saturday, the badge of the US consulate was removed, and on Sunday, a dark glass car left the consulate amid boos from passers-by.
On Sunday, many Chengdu people gathered in front of the US Consulate to take photos, and those who had not been there were also driven by curiosity about current events to take a look.
Agence France-Presse reporters from Chengdu Railway Station also went to observe near the US Consulate in Chengdu, and reported that there was an endless stream of curious people, and many parents took their children for a walk to watch the Consulate, take photos of buildings, or take selfies.
The consulate was surrounded by guards, and the police "corrected" people's behavior from time to time. They did not seem to allow any outrageous behavior: a woman was stopped as soon as she was preparing to sing red songs, and a guard confiscated a banner.
However, residents of a nearby residential building succeeded in pulling up a giant Chinese flag on their balcony and shouting slogans in support of China.
The US Consulate in Chengdu opened in 1985, covering all consular affairs of the United States in southwestern China, especially the Tibet Autonomous Region.
Agence France-Presse reporter from Chengdu station said that the Chinese government's response to the United States was relatively restrained: many Chinese people asked the government to close the US consulate in Hong Kong online, but the official only said that "closing the US consulate in Chengdu is a necessary and legal response to the unreasonable behavior of the United States".
At present, in addition to Chengdu, the United States has consulates in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan and Hong Kong in China.
Large-scale financial media action "Walking to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" starts-Today's Highlights-Hunan Daily Network-Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily, New Hunan Client, July 25 (Reporter) On July 25, the large-scale financial media action "Going to the Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation" sponsored by the Financial Program Center of the Central Radio and Television General Station started from Xuzhou, Jiangsu Province. Two caravans carrying 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system slowly drove out of the scene under the eyes of the guests at the scene.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that "2020 is a milestone year. We will build a well-off society in an all-round way and achieve the goal of the first century. 2020 is also the year of decisive battle against poverty".
The large-scale financial media action "Going to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" is an important measure taken by the Financial Program Center of the Central Radio and Television General Station to cooperate with this major theme and do a good job in poverty alleviation propaganda.
The action will go into poverty alleviation villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government across the country, dig out fresh poverty alleviation stories, directly attack the great changes in the appearance of villages and villages, and show how villagers break through the predicament of survival and development and move towards the road of becoming rich.
The operation will last for more than three months.
The reporter started from Xuzhou and divided into two roads, all the way to the southwest line, passing through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; The other road takes the northwest line, passing through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, with a journey of more than 10,000 kilometers.
In the form of reporting, "Walking to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" boldly integrates.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcast through CCTV Financial Channel, CCTV Economic Voice, China Traffic Radio and CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, the live TV broadcast will be mainly completed in the noon news program "Tianxia Finance" of CCTV Financial Channel (premiere time:12:00-13:00 from Monday to Sunday), and the prime-time news column "Economic Information Network" of CCTV Financial Channel will set up a poverty alleviation report column (premiere time:20:30-21:30 from Monday to Sunday).
At the same time, the caravan will broadcast live for up to one hour to each village on the CCTV financial client. The audience can watch the live broadcast and participate in the lottery by downloading the CCTV financial APP.
In terms of technology application and studio design, "Walking to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" has the courage to make a breakthrough and pioneered the "Outfield New Media Caravan".
The car is equipped with 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system, and uses 5G + 4K / 8K + AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, large screen and small screen, and TV broadcasting.
Equipped with Sanxun broadcasting area, the broadcasting area is converted from a container, with a length of 12 meters, a width of 2.55 meters and a height of 3.98 meters. The box adopts a hydraulic automatic deployment structure, which can turn up to 120 degrees.
The studio area can also be automatically expanded and an external expansion platform, covering an area of more than 50 square meters, can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
At present, Dongchuan District of Kunming City is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
Lv Ling, an employee of Kunming Aisfu Electronic Technology Company, said, "Now, as soon as you leave your home, you enter the factory door to make money and take care of your family. Thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the trade union."
Walking into the poverty alleviation workshop of electronic components processing in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a busy picture came into view.
Lv Ling, who is in her 40s, is a single mother. She takes care of her children alone and takes care of her elderly parents.
When she was in the most difficult time, Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped to come up with ideas and find ways to "send charcoal in the snow" after running.
Since 2018, Lv Ling has enjoyed housing, schooling, social security, employment and other assistance policies and assistance funds issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her child has successfully graduated and employed, and she herself has a job and income after taking part in skills training, and has been out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that the special skills training project of Dongchuan District General Organization to help fight poverty is part of the skills training work of Yunnan Federation of Trade Unions.
According to the characteristics of the workers in difficulty in the relocation and resettlement sites for poverty alleviation in the district, the district general manager made in-depth investigations to understand the training needs, determined the types of training jobs, and planned to train 450 electricians, welders and pastry chefs in the near future.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Agricultural Bank of Yunnan Menglian County Sub-branch, wrote a sincere thank-you letter to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In her letter, she sincerely thanked the trade union for giving her the golden autumn student aid from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident and her mother was included in the files of employees in difficulty. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the filing and card-setting policy.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been lifted out of difficulties through institutional guarantee and precise assistance.
The success of Lv Ling's family and Li Yi in getting rid of difficulties is a microcosm of Yunnan trade unions promoting the work of getting rid of difficulties for workers in difficulty.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Department of the Yunnan Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial general manager has strengthened the dynamic management of the files of employees in difficulty, promoted the normalization of filing work, and timely incorporated the difficult employees who meet the filing conditions into the assistance system; Broaden the application channels for employees in difficulty, and use WeChat to open an online filing service platform for employees in difficulty, so as to facilitate employees in difficulty to declare voluntarily in a timely manner.
During the epidemic period, it was difficult to go out to work. In order to help workers with difficulties in filing relieve the pressure of life, Yunnan Province has arranged a total of more than 13 million yuan to send warm funds. According to the standard of 2,000 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in filing at the national level and 1,500 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in filing at the provincial level, more than 6,000 national and 1,000 provincial workers with difficulties in filing have been given special warm condolences.
At the same time, the provincial general manager connects with various Internet recruitment platforms such as human and social departments and Zhaopin recruitment, pushes recruitment information to employees in difficulty, and provides employment consultation, employment guidance and other services.
